    "NLP is a multidisciplinary field that combines linguistics, computer science and machine learning to enable machines to interpret and generate human language.",
    "Early NLP systems relied heavily on rule-based methods, which required extensive domain knowledge and were limited in scalability.",
    "These were soon replaced by statistical approaches and simple neural networks like the perceptron (Rosenblatt, 1958), which could learn basic patterns from data.",
